cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes an adaptive tracking algorithm for object tracking in videos. The use of affine subspaces and Grassmann manifolds also suggests a strong mathematical and geometric component, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with video processing and analysis, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of tracking algorithms could also place it in the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as tracking is an important component of many robotic systems.
